# Spec-Kit Workflow (Agent Anchor)

This project uses **GitHub Spec-Kit** for Spec-Driven Development. Follow this workflow:

## Commands

- **`/speckit.constitution`** — Update project principles (`.specify/memory/constitution.md`)
- **`/speckit.specify`** — Create feature spec from natural language
- **`/speckit.plan`** — Create technical plan
- **`/speckit.tasks`** — Break plan into tasks
- **`/speckit.implement`** — Execute tasks

## Key Files

- `.specify/spec.md` — Project goals, requirements
- `.specify/plan.md` — Technical architecture
- `.specify/memory/constitution.md` — Project principles (MUST comply)
- `docs/PLAN.md` — Full development plan

## Before Coding

1. Ensure spec/plan exist for new features
2. Follow constitution principles (Electron process boundaries, Agent protocol, TypeScript strict)
3. SQLite only in main process; React only in renderer
